fn populate_priv(id: PrivId, entry: &BootEntry, n_active: u16) {
    let pr = unsafe { priv_slot_mut(id) }...;
    pr.proc_nr = Some(entry.nr);
    pr.flags = entry.priv_flags;

    if entry.trap_mask == SRV_T {
        fill_bits(&mut pr.ipc_to, n_active as usize);           // Line 374: Can send to [0, n_active)
        fill_bits(&mut pr.k_call_mask, NR_KERN_CALLS_PHASE3);   // Line 378: Can issue Phase-3 kcalls
    }
    pr.sig_mgr = boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR);  // RS manages signals
}
```

**Lines 408-417**: `fill_bits()` — bitmap initialization:
```rust
fn fill_bits(map: &mut [u32], n: usize) {
    for i in 0..n {
        let word = i / 32;
        let bit = i % 32;
        if word < map.len() {
            map[word] |= 1 << bit;        // Set bit i across word boundaries
        }
    }
}
```

This sets `ipc_to[0..2]` (two u32s covering 64 bits) for the first `n_active` (16) processes: SCHED gets bits set for SYSTEM, ASYNCM, IDLE, CLOCK, all servers, and INIT.

